📘 DOM Learning Cheat Sheet – "Chai aur Code Style"
🎯 Getting Elements

🌳 What is the DOM (Document Object Model)?

The DOM stands for Document Object Model.
It’s a way for your browser to understand and organize an HTML page — like a family tree.

👉 Think of it like this:

The HTML file you write is just text.

The DOM is how the browser turns that text into a structure it can work with.

It represents your web page as objects (like <html>, <body>, <p>, etc.) arranged in a tree.
js
// Get element by ID
const title = document.getElementById('title');

// Get the first element matching a selector
document.querySelector('#title');       // By ID
document.querySelector('.test');        // By class
document.querySelector('title');        // By tag
document.querySelector('input[type="password"]'); // By attribute

// Get all matching elements (returns NodeList)
const items = document.querySelectorAll('li');

// Get elements by class (returns HTMLCollection)
const htmlCol = document.getElementsByClassName('list-item');

🔍 Accessing Attributes
title.id;                      // 'title'
title.className;               // 'test' (after update)

title.getAttribute('id');      // 'title'
title.getAttribute('class');   // 'test'

// Set attribute
title.setAttribute('class', 'test');
🎨 Styling Elements
title.style.backgroundColor = 'green';
items[0].style.color = 'white';
items[0].style.color = 'black';

// Looping through NodeList
items.forEach(function (item) {
    item.style.backgroundColor = 'green';
});
For HTMLCollection:

const htmlArr = Array.from(htmlCol);
htmlArr.forEach((item) => {
    item.style.backgroundColor = 'red';
});

📝 Text Content
title.innerText;    // Only visible text → 'DOM learning on Chai aur code'
title.textContent;  // All text, including hidden → 'DOM learning on Chai aur code test text'

// Updating text
items[0].innerText = '69';


📌 Notes
querySelector() selects the first match only.

querySelectorAll() returns a NodeList (can use .forEach).

getElementsByClassName() returns an HTMLCollection (convert to array with Array.from()).

innerText ignores hidden text. textContent includes it.

Use element.style.propertyName to change inline CSS styles.

🧠 Memory Boost
"Use getElement for direct IDs, querySelector for flexible matchups. innerText sees, textContent knows. Always style with .style.property!"
